# System Architecture

## Overview

The prototype is designed as a simplified Earthquake Early Warning System (EEWS) using embedded sensing, signal processing, and machine learning.

---

## System Flow

Geophone Sensor
↓
Amplifier Circuit
↓
ADS1115 ADC
↓
Raspberry Pi
↓
Signal Processing
↓
Feature Extraction
↓
Machine Learning Classification
↓
Early Warning Logic
↓
Alert Output

---

## Main Functional Blocks

### 1. Signal Acquisition

The geophone captures vibration signals from surrounding motion and converts them into electrical signals.

---

### 2. Signal Amplification

The amplifier increases low-level seismic signals for easier ADC reading and processing.

---

### 3. Analog-to-Digital Conversion

The ADS1115 converts analog seismic signals into digital values readable by the Raspberry Pi.

---

### 4. Signal Processing

The Raspberry Pi filters and processes incoming signals before extracting useful features.

---

### 5. Feature Extraction

The system extracts statistical and frequency-domain features including:

- RMS
- Mean
- Standard deviation
- FFT frequency components
- Zero crossing rate

---

### 6. Machine Learning Classification

The AI model classifies signals into categories such as:

- Noise
- P-wave-like signal
- S-wave-like signal

---

### 7. Early Warning Logic

If a P-wave-like signal is detected before an S-wave-like signal, the system can trigger an early warning countdown simulation.
